result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jeovany Gonzalez Espinoza in court.  Attorney Kathryn E. Keizer in court for Jeovany Gonzalez Espinoza.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by ADA Samuel Berg. Called @ 1:33 p.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for initial appearance as to both files - 22CM476 & 22CT431. Record by Atty. Keizer who has gone over the charges and penalties with the defendant and enters not guilty pleas as to all charges. Court sets matters out for status in about 60 days. Court in recess.
Status conference scheduled for November 15, 2022 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant Jeovany Gonzalez Espinoza not in court - Authorization on file.  Attorney Kathryn E. Keizer in court for Jeovany Gonzalez Espinoza.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by ADA TenHaken. Called @ 3:57 p.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for plea and sentencing, but Atty. was informed that State was filing new charges. State provides complaints to Atty. Court waives appearance of defendant as to the new charges and instructs Atty. Keizer to file authorizations on those. Atty. Keizer asks that all matter be set over so she can go over the charges and penalties on new cases with the defendant. Court in recess.
Initial appearance scheduled for September 19, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
